# ── Python ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.pyo
*.log

# ── Virtual environment — NEVER commit this ───────────────────────────────────
.venv/
venv/
env/

# ── Frontend build artifacts — NEVER commit these ─────────────────────────────
node_modules/
dist/
.vite/

# ── Claude Code tool state — not project content ──────────────────────────────
.claude/

# ── Stray local files, not part of the app ─────────────────────────────────────
/ALPHA25_BLACK7.png
/Jul*.png

# ── Dev-only raw data — inputs to the offline pipeline (notebooks 01-14),
# never read by the running API (main.py / copilot_engine.py / live_signals.py),
# and 496MB combined — nowhere near appropriate for a deploy repo. Paths are
# anchored under backend/ since that's where .gitignore's mid-path patterns
# actually resolve from (repo root, not backend/) ─────────────────────────────
backend/data/raw/sentiment/
backend/data/raw/stocks/

# GDELT per-ticker parquets are re-created by fetch_news.py and unused at
# runtime, BUT all_news.parquet IS read live by /market-sentiment and
# /market-news (load_news() in main.py) — keep that one file.
backend/data/raw/news/*.parquet
!backend/data/raw/news/all_news.parquet

# ── Dev-only / legacy processed files — intermediate pipeline artifacts or
# superseded-by-newer-file outputs, never read by the running API ────────────
backend/data/processed/features_stock.csv
backend/data/processed/final_dataset.csv
backend/data/processed/*_clean.csv
backend/data/processed/wsb_clean.csv
backend/data/processed/wsb_emotion.csv
backend/data/processed/wsb_sentiment.csv
backend/data/processed/gdelt_sentiment.csv
backend/data/processed/yahoo_news_clean.csv
backend/data/processed/yahoo_news_sentiment.csv

# features_finance.csv / features_sentiment.csv are NOT excluded — main.py
# and copilot_engine.py read them directly at runtime (OHLCV history,
# indicator lookups, the per-ticker accuracy track record) and there is no
# server-side path to regenerate them (build_features.py needs the raw data
# excluded above), so they have to actually ship. ~58MB and ~63MB — both
# comfortably under GitHub's 100MB single-file limit.

# ── Legacy model files — superseded by the current naming (xgb_finance.pkl
# etc.), not loaded by any current code path ──────────────────────────────────
backend/data/models/xgboost_model.pkl
backend/data/models/scaler.pkl
backend/data/models/scaler_lstm.pkl
backend/data/models/transformer_lstm.pt

# lstm_finance.pt / lstm_sentiment.pt are NOT excluded — tiny (45-52KB) and
# needed for the Live Mode feature. Every other trained model file (XGBoost,
# Random Forest, Logistic Regression, GRU, TransformerEncoder) is well under
# 1MB each — none of them need special handling.

# ── Prediction CSVs and metrics — DO commit these. There's no retraining
# step on Render, so the app serves whatever predictions ship in the repo.
# backend/data/predictions/*.csv
# backend/data/predictions/model_metrics.json

# ── Secrets — real API keys live here locally + in Render/Vercel env vars,
# never in git. backend/.env.example documents the required variable with
# a blank value; frontend/.env is a pre-existing exception (see note there).
backend/.env

# ── OS / Editor ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.vscode/
*.code-workspace
